cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper proposes an edge content delivery framework based on mobile edge computing, which involves network architecture and communication protocols. 
2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The proposed framework involves distributed caching and content delivery mechanisms, which are relevant to this sub-category. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a cache pool ranking mechanism based on content popularity, which involves data structures and algorithms. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed framework involves system design and control mechanisms for efficient content delivery and update. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the quality of experience (QoE) of mobile users, which is related to multimedia content delivery.
